-- Etihad Airways Places $4.3 Billion Order for Engines, Maintenance With GE
-- Arif Sharif
-- 2010-07-20T14:07:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-20/etihad-airways-places-4-3-billion-order-for-engines-maintenance-with-ge.html

          
          
             Etihad Airways, an Abu Dhabi
government-owned company, placed a $1.8 billion order for 78
GEnx-1B engines from General Electric Co. to power 35 Boeing
787s it ordered last year, it said in an e-mailed statement.  
 Etihad also signed a 15-year agreement with GE Aviation for
the maintenance, repair and overhaul of these engines valued at
more than $2.5 billion, it said today.  
